{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bcee7b8f-4797-4be2-8e54-cbe0f49cb5f8","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory. Since this is a general guidance question, here's what you need to change:\n\n### 1. **NuGet.org setup**\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a new trusted publisher linking your GitHub repo, workflow file, and optionally an environment\n\n### 2. **Workflow changes**\n\n**Add OIDC permission** to your job:\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # required for OIDC token\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**Replace** your `dotnet nuget push` step. Instead of:\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Use:**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n  env:\n    NUGET_AUTH_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}  # not needed; see below\n```\n\nActually, the correct approach is:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet (trusted publishing)\n  run: |\n    dotnet nuget add source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json \\\n      --name nuget.org \\\n      --username \"az\" \\\n      --password \"${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\" \\\n      --store-password-in-clear-text\n    dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source nuget.org\n```\n\nOr more simply, use the **official pattern**:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet\n  run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n  env:\n    # No API key needed — OIDC token is exchanged automatically\n    DOTNET_NUGET_SIGNATURE_VERIFICATION: true\n```\n\n### 3. **Remove the secret**\nOnce verified, delete `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repo's **Settings → Secrets**.\n\n### Summary of changes\n| Before | After |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` in push | No secret needed |\n| No `permissions` block | `id-token: write` added |\n| No NuGet.org trusted publisher | Trusted publisher configured on nuget.org |\n\nThe key idea: OIDC lets GitHub prove the workflow's identity to NuGet.org without a long-lived API key. Would you like me to create or modify a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3bed1ded-e467-402f-9f3e-8aec2765f22a","outputTokens":634,"requestId":"E427:2950B:69B1A7C:720A28F:6A03CCD2"},"id":"5bbcca1e-c4c5-492c-be03-b9f03e90b48a","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:59:11.525Z","parentId":"d4cc993e-13a2-4103-a517-a6fdfdd34c3a"}
